                  <h3>Committees</h3>

                  <p>FIBHIOS has a corporate governance structure in line with international standards, and above the provisions stated by the Ley del Mercado de Valores for publicly traded companies. It seeks to ensure transparency and effectiveness in its management, while achieving a strict alignment of incentives between the External Manager and our certificate holders.</p>
                  <p>The following chart depicts the structure of FIBHIOS’s management bodies:</p>
                  <img src="/images/fibhios/contenidos/comites-en.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block">
                  <h3>Compensation Committee (CC)</h3>
                      <p>The Technical Committee must appoint from among its members 3 persons, one of which shall be independent, to be on the Compensation Committee, which has the following functions:</p>
                      <ul class="ck-po">
                      <li>Reviewing the compensation policies and fees to be paid to the External Manager, Technical Committee Directors (including independent members), and any relevant third party</li>
                      <li>Evaluating the performance of the Technical Committee Directors</li>
                      <li>Identifying and assessing candidates to be elected as Directors to the Technical Committee </li>
                      <li>Issuing recommendations to the External Manager and the Certificate Holders General Meeting about candidates to be elected, appointed, or removed as Technical Committee Directors</li>
                      <li>Proposing the emoluments to be paid to the independent Directors of the Technical Committee at the Certificate Holders General Meeting</li>
                      <li>Advising on the selection criteria for new members of the Technical Committee, management, and external advisors</li>
                    </ul>
